rComments: Not a very good lecturer. Do not read the last review, it was false and I suffered. The class was supposed to be taught in English but half the times it feels like you're sitting in a French class. Lectures are very disorganized and concepts covered are not clear or left ambiguous. Tough marker and not very helpful.

Speaks English well enough, but doesn't seem to completely grasp the intricacies of the language, especially on exams. Is a terrible orator and her lectures are very disorganised as she fumbles through the material with little ability to make points clear and concise. This wouldn't be a problem if she provided real online slides, but she refuses to

A nice young teacher, tried to cater to the age of students by making casual jokes and having a relaxed approach. People disrespectfully talked over her though. Seems interested in the subject and likes teaching. Gave a easy 10% extra on a midterm if you wrote a small reflection.  She just wants you to pass and be interested in Canadian History.
